Package sh.brane.rpc

Record Class JsonRpcResponse

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
sh.brane.rpc.JsonRpcResponse
Record Components:
jsonrpc - the JSON-RPC version (always "2.0")
result - the result object if successful, or null if error
error - the error object if failed, or null if successful
id - the request ID that this response corresponds to
public record JsonRpcResponse(String jsonrpc, @Nullable Object result, @Nullable JsonRpcError error, String id) extends Record
Represents a JSON-RPC 2.0 response from an Ethereum node.

This record holds the response from a JSON-RPC call, which may contain either a successful result or an error. Use hasError() to check which is present.

Accessing Results:

  • resultAsString() - for simple string results (e.g., eth_chainId)
  • resultAsMap() - for object results (e.g., eth_getBlockByNumber)
  • resultAsList() - for array results (e.g., eth_getLogs)
  • resultAs(Class) - for typed conversion using Jackson
Since:
0.1.0-alpha
